        "timestamp": "2018-10-16 19:17:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nI was only able to test:\naai           \t1       \tTue Oct 16 18:14:52 2018\tDEPLOYED\taai-3.0.0           \tonap\nappc          \t1       \tTue Oct 16 18:51:28 2018\tDEPLOYED\tappc-3.0.0          \tonap\nclamp         \t1       \tTue Oct 16 19:13:35 2018\tDEPLOYED\tclamp-3.0.0         \tonap\ndmaap         \t1       \tTue Oct 16 18:58:07 2018\tDEPLOYED\tdmaap-3.0.0         \tonap\nmsb           \t3       \tTue Oct 16 18:59:44 2018\tDEPLOYED\tmsb-3.0.0           \tonap\nportal        \t1       \tTue Oct 16 18:49:31 2018\tDEPLOYED\tportal-3.0.0        \tonap\nrobot         \t1       \tTue Oct 16 18:52:02 2018\tDEPLOYED\trobot-3.0.0         \tonap\nsdc           \t1       \tTue Oct 16 18:53:37 2018\tDEPLOYED\tsdc-3.0.0           \tonap\nsdnc          \t1       \tTue Oct 16 18:51:36 2018\tDEPLOYED\tsdnc-3.0.0          \tonap\nso            \t1       \tTue Oct 16 18:42:19 2018\tDEPLOYED\tso-3.0.0            \tonap\n\nby setting the following in values.yaml\nservice:\n  type: ClusterIP\n\nThe others may or may not have the same problem.  If they do, its usually that externalPort is missing from values.yaml",
